item.description:
arXiv:2402.18410v2 Announce Type: replace Abstract: At present, there are several measurements of $B$ decays that exhibit discrepancies with the predictions of the Standard Model, and suggest the presence of new physics in $b	o s$ and $b 	o c(u)$ quark level transitions. Motivated by the prospects of the ongoing high-luminosity $B$ factories, we study the exclusive $B 	o a_1 (1260) \ell^-  ar{
u}_\ell$ process within the Standard Model Effective Field Theory (SMEFT) formalism, to understand the sensitivity of new physics. The new physics parameters are constrained by using the experimental branching fractions of the (semi)leptonic $B 	o \ell  ar{
u}$ and $B 	o (\pi, ho, \omega) \ell  ar{
u}$ processes (where $\ell = e, \mu, 	au$) which undergo $b 	o u \ell  ar{
u}$ quark level transitions. We then perform a comprehensive angular analysis of the exclusive $B 	o a_1 (1260) \ell^-  ar{
u}_\ell$ process in the Standard Model and in the presence of various new physics operators. We also provide the predictions and comment on various observables, such as branching ratio, forward-backward asymmetry, and the test of lepton flavor non universality of the $B 	o a_1 (1260) \ell^-  ar{
u}_\ell$ channel.
